  <p>Bitcoin has been locked in an extraordinarily tight trading range for over four hours. After reaching a fresh June 3 low of <strong>$66,301</strong> during the Asian morning session, BTC has oscillated between $66,300 and $66,400 ” a range of just <strong>$100</strong> ” for the entire session.</p>

  <p>This is not your typical consolidation. This is textbook <strong>range compression</strong>, and it has been building for twice as long as we flagged in our midday update. The spring is wound tighter. The question is not <em>if</em> the breakout happens ” it's <em>which direction</em> and <em>how violent</em> the move will be.</p>

  <h2>Current Market Snapshot</h2>

  <p>The entire crypto market is in a holding pattern. Meme coins are showing tentative signs of stabilization, with DOGE, PEPE, and BONK all trading within narrow bands alongside BTC. The 24-hour damage remains severe ” meme coins are down 7-8% ” but the bleeding has stopped for now.</p>

  <div class="key-level">
    <div class="level"><span class="label">Current Price</span><span class="value">$66,393</span></div>
    <div class="level"><span class="label">24h Low</span><span class="value">$66,301</span></div>
    <div class="level"><span class="label">24h High</span><span class="value">$70,580</span></div>
    <div class="level"><span class="label">24h Change</span><span class="value bearish">-5.96%</span></div>
    <div class="level"><span class="label">Consolidation Range</span><span class="value">$66,300 ” $66,400</span></div>
    <div class="level"><span class="label">Range Duration</span><span class="value">4+ Hours</span></div>
  </div>

  <h2>What 4+ Hours of Range Compression Means</h2>

  <p>In technical analysis, the longer price compresses in a tight range, the more explosive the eventual breakout. There is a direct relationship between consolidation duration and breakout magnitude. A 4-hour range compression at these levels is significant for three reasons:</p>

  <ol>
    <li><strong>Energy accumulation:</strong> Every minute BTC stays in this range, buy and sell pressure build beneath the surface. The trapped energy must eventually release.</li>
    <li><strong>Liquidity pooling:</strong> Stop-loss orders accumulate just below $66,000 and above $66,500. When price finally breaks, these clustered stops trigger cascading moves.</li>
    <li><strong>Time decay of uncertainty:</strong> The longer the range holds without breaking down, the more sidelined capital begins to view $66.3K as a legitimate floor ” setting up a potential short squeeze to the upside.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Key Levels to Watch</h2>

  <div class="key-level">
    <div class="level"><span class="label">�� Critical Support</span><span class="value bearish">$66,000</span></div>
    <div class="level"><span class="label">�Ÿ� Immediate Support</span><span class="value bearish">$66,300 (range floor)</span></div>
    <div class="level"><span class="label">�Ÿ� Current Range</span><span class="value">$66,300 - $66,400</span></div>
    <div class="level"><span class="label">�Ÿ� Range Ceiling</span><span class="value bullish">$66,400 - $66,500</span></div>
    <div class="level"><span class="label">�Ÿ� First Resistance</span><span class="value bullish">$66,784 (pre-breakdown level)</span></div>
    <div class="level"><span class="label">�Ÿ� Major Resistance</span><span class="value bullish">$67,000</span></div>
